## ⚙️ Requirements

### R Packages

The following R packages are required:

* survival
* glmnet
* timeROC
* Rcpp
* RcppArmadillo
* openxlsx
* dplyr

All required packages are automatically installed within the scripts if missing.

---

## 🚀 How to Run

### 1. Clone the repository

```
git clone https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/YOUR_REPO.git
cd YOUR_REPO
```

---

### 2. Run Simulation Study

```
source("cox_simulation_lasso.R")
```

This script:

* Generates synthetic time-dependent survival data
* Fits AACD and LASSO models
* Computes performance metrics (FP, FN, Precision, Recall, F1)
* Saves results into an Excel file

---

### 3. Run Real Data Analysis (PBC Dataset)

```
source("pbc_realdata_analysis.R")
```

This script:

* Constructs time-dependent covariates using `tmerge`
* Fits both AACD and glmnet LASSO models
* Computes:

  * C-index
  * Time-dependent AUC (1, 3, 5 years)
  * Coefficients and standard errors
* Saves results to:

```
Results_PBC_DataSet.xlsx
```

---

## 🧠 Methodology

### AACD Algorithm

The proposed method is based on:

* **Adaptive Active-set Coordinate Descent (AACD)**
* Efficient computation of the **regularization path**
* Model selection using **BIC / EBIC**

### Key Features

* Handles **time-dependent covariates**
* Scalable to **high-dimensional settings (p >> n)**
* Faster convergence compared to standard methods

---

## 📊 Outputs

### Simulation Study

* Mean and standard deviation of coefficients
* False Positives (FP), False Negatives (FN)
* Precision, Recall, F1-score
* Runtime statistics

### Real Data Analysis

* Model coefficients + standard errors
* C-index
* Time-dependent AUC
* Execution time

---

## 📈 Dataset

### PBC Dataset

The real data analysis uses the **Primary Biliary Cirrhosis (PBC)** dataset from the `survival` package:

* Includes longitudinal measurements
* Converted into time-dependent format using `tmerge`
* Widely used benchmark in survival analysis

